{{Infobox political party |name = Jewish Economic Party |founded = October 1925 |founders = Slovak Jewish Orthodox rabbis |country = Czechoslovakia }} The '''Jewish Economic Party''' was a political party of the [[First Czechoslovak Republic]]. It was created in October 1925 by Slovak Jewish Orthodox rabbis as a regional [[Slovakia]]n party against the Zionist-controlled [[Jewish Party (Czechoslovakia)|Jewish Party]]. It took part in the [[Czechoslovak parliamentary election, 1925 |1925 Czechoslovak parliamentary elections]], where it got 16,861 votes (0.24%) and no seat.
