'''Rodolfo Acevedo''' (13 June 1951 – 17 February 2012)<ref>{{citation |contribution-url= http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/spanish/pdf/language-materials/10386chl_spa.pdf?lang=spa |contribution= Facllece Historiador de la Inglesia, Rodolfo Acevedo |title= Noticia de la Iglesa Chile |publisher= LDS Church |date=June 2012 |language= es |page= N3 }}</ref> was a [[Chile]]an [[Latter-day Saint]] author. He wrote the book ''Los Mormones en Chile'' (''The Mormons in Chile'').  He also wrote ''Alturas Sagradas'', a history of the [[Santiago Chile Temple]] of [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]] (LDS Church). He originally wrote this work as his thesis at the [[Pontifical Catholic University of Chile]].

Acevedo joined the LDS Church in [[San Antonio, Chile]] in 1968.  His home was used as the location for an early-morning seminary class in the 1970s.<ref>{{citation |first= Judy C. |last= Olsen |url= http://www.lds.org/ensign/1999/10/blossoming-as-the-rose-in-latin-america?lang=eng |title= Blossoming as the Rose in Latin America |journal= [[Ensign (LDS magazine)|Ensign]] |date=October 1999 |page= 47 }}</ref>  For a time he worked as a teacher at the church-owned Deseret School in Chile.  In 1999 Acevedo was serving as director of public affairs for the Chile Area of the church.<ref>{{citation |url= http://www.ldschurchnewsarchive.com/articles/35747/Cover-Story-Pres-Hinckley-in-Chile-marks-largest-LDS-gathering.html |title= Pres. Hinckley in Chile marks largest LDS gathering |newspaper= [[Church News]] |first= Rodolfo |last= Acevedo |date= May 8, 1999 }}</ref>

Acevedo was a [[Bishop (Latter Day Saints)|bishop]] of the LDS Church.  In 2006, he was serving as the [[Patriarch (Latter Day Saints)|patriarch]] of the [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]] Chile Puente Alto [[Stake (Latter Day Saints)|Stake]].

